==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[cylix]]

===Etymology===
from the Greek ''kulix'' (cup)

===Pronunciation===
kaɪlɪks (''pl.'' kaɪlɪkiz ''or'' kaɪlɪksəz)

===Noun===
'''kylix''' (''pl.'' '''kylikes''' ''or'' '''kylixes''')

# An Ancient Grecian drinking cup with a stem, two handles, and a broad, shallow body

====Usage notes====
The dig team unearthed a '''kylix''' at the site in Bergama

